<task id="task-9820" class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">In Manual view </title><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><steps class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Open a test case in <uicontrol conkeyref="ks-UI-text/ks-ui-manual" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "/> view.</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click on the drop-down icon of the <uicontrol conkeyref="ks-UI-text/ks-ui-add" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "/> button, then choose <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Exception Handling Statements</uicontrol>.</cmd><stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp "><image href="https://github.com/katalon-studio/docs-images/raw/master/katalon-studio/docs/statements/exception-handling-statements.png" scope="external" width="500" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">exception handling statement</alt></image></stepxmp></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">To add a keyword under a statement, select that statement, then click <uicontrol conkeyref="ks-UI-text/ks-ui-add" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "/>. A test step is created under that statement.</cmd><stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp "><image href="https://github.com/katalon-studio/docs-images/raw/master/katalon-studio/docs/statements/exception-handling.png" scope="external" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">exception handling statements in manual view</alt></image></stepxmp><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">Refer to the following table for the usage of each statement:<table class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry class="- topic/entry ">Statement</entry><entry class="- topic/entry ">Description</entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry class="- topic/entry ">Try</entry><entry class="- topic/entry ">This statement indicates that all steps within is monitored by exception handlers.</entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry class="- topic/entry ">Throw</entry><entry class="- topic/entry ">Some code must throw an exception before you can <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Catch</b> an exception. Regardless of what code throws the exception, it always involves the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Throw</b> statement.</entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry class="- topic/entry ">Catch</entry><entry class="- topic/entry ">When there is any issue occurred during the execution of the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Try</b> block, Katalon Studio executes all steps within.</entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry class="- topic/entry ">Finally</entry><entry class="- topic/entry ">This is the last part of the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Try-Catch-Finally</b></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></info></step></steps></taskbody></task>